{"id":4558,"date":"2023-12-08T15:46:52","date_gmt":"2023-12-08T04:46:52","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/?post_type=help_centre&#038;p=4558"},"modified":"2023-12-08T15:49:10","modified_gmt":"2023-12-08T04:49:10","slug":"pairing-the-remote-control","status":"publish","type":"help_centre","link":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/help-centre\/troubleshooting\/pairing-the-remote-control\/","title":{"rendered":"Pairing the remote control"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>To pair your remote with the Stoke Foil&#8217;s main unit, follow these steps:<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><strong>Ensure the Main Battery is Disconnected:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Start by disconnecting the main battery from the main unit to ensure a safe and controlled pairing process.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"2\"><li><strong>Power On the Remote Control:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Turn on the remote control while the main battery is still disconnected.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"3\"><li><strong>Enter Menu Mode:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Hold down the power level\/menu button (the one with the three dots) until the remote displays &#8220;Pairing.&#8221; This indicates that you have entered menu mode.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"4\"><li><strong>Initiate Pairing Mode:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>While in menu mode, hold down the menu button again to enter pairing mode specifically. Release the menu button once you see the &#8220;Pairing&#8221; message on the remote.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"5\"><li><strong>Attach Main Battery to the Main Unit:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Now, attach the main battery to the main unit. You will observe a message on the remote indicating that pairing has succeeded, and the signal strength will be displayed.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"6\"><li><strong>Verify Pairing Success:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Occasionally, the pairing process may require two attempts, but in most cases, you should achieve success on the first try.<\/p><h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Throttle Calibration (If Needed)<\/h4><p>In the rare event that your remote is not unlocking or the throttle range is not from 0-100%, you can perform a throttle calibration. Follow these steps:<\/p><p>Power On the Remote Control:<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><strong>Turn on the remote control using the power level\/menu button.<\/strong><\/li>\n\n<li><strong>Enter Menu Mode:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Hold down the power level\/menu button until the display shows &#8220;Pairing,&#8221; indicating that you are in menu mode.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"3\"><li><strong>Navigate to Throttle Calibration:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Use the three dots button to cycle through the menu options until &#8220;Throttle Calibration&#8221; is displayed.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"4\"><li><strong>Initiate Throttle Calibration Mode:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Hold down the menu button again to enter throttle calibration mode. Release the menu button.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"5\"><li><strong>Calibrate the Throttle:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Pull the trigger through its full range, from 0% to 100%, and then release the trigger.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"6\"><li><strong>Exit Calibration Mode:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Click the power button once to exit throttle calibration mode.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"7\"><li><strong>Exit Menu Mode:<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Click the power button again to exit the menu mode.<\/p><p>By following these steps, you can successfully pair your remote with the main unit and, if necessary, perform throttle calibration for optimal performance.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>To pair your remote with the Stoke Foil&#8217;s main unit, follow these steps: Start by disconnecting the main battery from the main unit to ensure a safe and controlled pairing process. Turn on the remote control while the main battery is still disconnec